Rogan v. Twenty-Third St. R. Co. (Common Pleas of New York City and County, General Term. November 11, 1892.) Action by Thomas Rogan against the Twenty-Third Street Railroad Company.

Argued before Daly, C. J., and Bookstaver and Bischoff, JJ.

No opinion. Exceptions overruled, and judgment ordered for the plaintiff.
